review_text:
Banque Populaire on Avenue Belgique has two ATM machines located in a safe area next to the front entrance.

This bank is one of the largest banks in Morocco and has currency exchange services. It is just down the road from Cafe La Tulipe and Emsallah.

I reduced my original rating of four stars to two in September 2018 after using the ATM machine and being shocked at the poor exchange rate given compared to BMCI and SociÃ©tÃ© GÃ©nÃ©rale. The rate was only 8.97 for one U.S. Dollar while the other banks' rates were 9.17, on the same day.

This is definitely not acceptable. I wonder why this big difference compared to other Moroccan banks in the exchange rates given at ATM machines.

Thus, I have decided never again to withdraw any money at any Banque Populaire location. The banks need to be regulated. It seems almost like thievery.

I would avoid withdrawing money from your foreign bank at any Banque Populaire. Go to any other major bank and get more money from your ATM transaction.

An absolute shame!!!!!!
The lady working in the back office (second row) is simply unacceptable. No willingness to help, no listening â€” his only goal seems to be to get rid of the customer as quickly as possible. She didn't even bother to check incoming mail, claiming with cold contempt that "your correspondence isn't here." It was only when I insisted firmly â€” due to lack of time and with supporting evidence â€” that, miraculously, the mail was suddenly found.

This behavior represents the height of incompetence, rudeness and complete disregard for customers.
This is not a passing lack, but a deeply rooted attitude: preserving personal comfort at the expense of service. Working as little as possible is their approach. The customer is simply annoying.

A team that does not aim for customer satisfaction, but only for their own peace of mind.
The bank will be changed at the first opportunity.

More precisely the Chaabi bank located on the main road of Bni Drar commune of Oujda. This bank has caused several victims, the majority of whom are Moroccan nationals or tourists. The ATM is programmed to debit money from the victim's account without issuing any notes. The victim sees that the operation is refused and leaves without suspicion. It was only later that she discovered that the amount requested from the ATM had been debited. No recourse is possible with the bank. The ATM is there like a trap set for victims.
Never contact this bank, whatever the transaction you want to carry out. The two main accomplices in these scams are the director and the cashier manager. The competent authorities should investigate these scams committed in this bank and which continue to this day. Having spoken with the guard of this bank, he knows a lot. If you are a victim of this bank, say so. Don't give up. These people have no scruples. These people are tarnishing the image of our country. They must be ruled out.
Greetings, servants, may God give them health and may God have mercy on the parents

I live in France and opened an account at BMCE for 7 years. For 3 years I have been requesting an access code to manage my account from my platform. I never got a response. In October 2023 during the All Saints holidays, I took the whole family. Knowing that I have the sum of 130,000 dirhams in my account, I went to withdraw a small amount. I learned that my account has been locked since April 2023, 6 months ago. Without my being informed, my account was hacked, the sum of 120,000 dirhams were drained from it by scammers. Seeing that I was not the originator of his transfers, they blocked the account late. In a single day there were 5 transactions of 20,000 dirhams each.
When I asked the director of the agency for explanations. Aucubrvteponse from him and no advice on how to get my money back. The only thing I could do is file a complaint at the police station and the Berkane court.
When I returned to France, I sent 25 emails without receiving a response from them. I alerted the intermediary agency in Orleans, also sent emails to their colleagues at the Berkane agency and received no response from this director. They advised him to file a complaint against the agency and don director. I conclude that this agency is in on it. Involve the Berkane judicial police, it can only be them who are behind this scam. I'm still waiting for a solution.

review_text:
I have had my account in this seat for more than eight years; the former director Mr. Saahaqi was professional and very friendly after his retirement, Mr. ELHILALI was appointed as director of this agency. Frankly, nothing to say, Mr. Elhilali is very nice, friendly and professional, he knew how to manage his teams well. Without forgetting Miss Soukeina, she is super nice, friendly, plus she has a knowledge of how to live and do which encourages customers to always come to her bravooo...
It's even a week ago that I learned again that this agent is no longer with me:-( It didn't take long for my mishaps, the people on the reception board are incompetent, rude, are not capable of constructing a sentence properly in French, it's sad:-(
we cling to our noses on the phone:-(. Unfortunately the only person who had the knowledge to live and do also from Mr. Elhilali's team was not present:-( our kind, kind Miss Soukeina was on vacation:-( we saw the effect of the change in personnel and I experienced a crappy situation with a team who never heard or knew what customer service and know-how means. how.
Lead, lead, supervise, coach a team on a daily basis. knowing how to analyze the situation to make the right decision for better customer service is not currently present in this agency.
It's aberrant, here it works differently compared to other countries, it's the banker who speaks, raises his voice, plays with his cell phone, eats in front of the customers, under the pretext, you only have to wait or leave; Moreover, I am a substitute and the director is not there. The queue is long, customers say it's been two hours of waiting and maybe more... But what a scandal!! I'm hallucinating, I've never experienced this in Europe, even Dubai and Oman either, it only exists in Morocco. You want to withdraw your money, no one owes you anything and they treat you like...

In short: A manager must also be exemplary at all levels and particularly in terms of advice and the quality of his sales, which has become essential for the image of the bank and the sustainability of the commercial relationship with the client. THIS IS LOGICAL BUT IN THIS SEAT THE PRESENCE OF THESE POINTS IS ZERO. DAMAGE.

PS. I am mostly German-speaking and English-speaking
BEST WISHES

review_text:
Good morning ,

Today I went to the Ouled Saleh agency to make a money withdrawal, with my national identity card at 12:00 p.m.
On arrival a security agent asks me the purpose of my visit, I tell him 'a withdrawal', he replies 'revealed', I specify "no, withdrawal", and I translate into Arabic 'bghite ntiri l flous ', there he asks me to wait outside in the blazing heat...I wait exactly an hour (knowing that I have serious health problems) before entering and when my turn arrives, I present my national card to the customer service representative and asks her for a withdrawal, there she takes the card and after tapping on her computer, almost throws the card in front of me, and says to me in a loud and inappropriate tone "no no no, today I only serve local, go find a large agency we don't have enough liquidity" then I answer him "I don't understand, it's an operation that I'm used to doing" , she said to me â€œyes but today no", I tell her "ok you can give me how much", she tells me "nothing", I tell her "do you think it's normal that I wait an hour for that", there she responds 'a really loud tone "I don't know what you are waiting for, ana 3i kheddama hena, go next..", I say ok I want to speak to the director, she tells me, he has gone to pray.

I apologize if I was long, I don't want to harm anyone, so I relay the facts as they happened and leave it to you to judge.
If I have to summarize:
Why explain the purpose of my visit to a security guard?
Why am I being refused a service provided by my bank?
Why am I experiencing this humiliation from a so-called account manager?

Note that another incident preceded this one, where in the same agency, a security agent told me that the system is down and when I insisted on entering, a customer service representative told him "don't no one comes home, aw syeda ma tghedach", it was 2 p.m....

review_text:
I went there to exchange USD. The service was very slow to begin with. However, I need my money exchanged so I waited.
I handed over my USD and she did the math in the computer and did not give me a receipt but rather counted my money and handed over to me. The money seemed less than the exchange rate posted so I asked for my receipt. She gave me my receipt after a dirty look plus another 200 dirham. I looked up my total on the receipt and counted my money again and I was still short 80 dirham. I asked her again and this time she got all pissed off. Took the money from me and finally gave me the correct amount. This is my 14th day in morroco and so far this was the only time I was about to get scammed and that with a famous bank.

Avoid if possible please.

location: Avenue Lalla Aicha Av Al Massira, Rue Boujdour, Essaouira 44000, Morocco
review_text: I wanted to retrieve money from an ATM inside the bank. The machine stated it's out of order, and a woman behind a counter said it had a problem. Then i used another ATM outside (also labeled with CIH Bank) that ATM debited my card, but it had a mechanical problem and did not open the money slot. Luckily, I have a receipt, on which is printed that the ATM has a problem and the transaction failed. That my card was debited before the ATM successfully finished the transaction, shows some fundamental procedural problems in such a trivial, every-day banking process. The woman at the counter was totally unhelpful when I explained this and said she told me there was a problem, it's my problem, I should raise a complaint with a letter. I told her I used the other ATM outside and why do they not put a sign on it or take it offline when they know it has a problem? She did not care in the least. I will clear the wrongful debiting of my credit card with my bank, but I could do without that kind of hassle on my holidays. This bank is pairing negligence with criminal incompetence and hostility towards ripped off customers. Worst banking experience in decades. Just stay away from this place. You can use the ATM 30meters farther, but that one charges 650 Dirhams for the same transaction, which is double the regular rate in Morocco
